{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772072085,"nonce":"uNIYCw/+oE7JI3MoVXDTL8zWPNM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87t_iGC","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/267","origin":"github"},"title":"Add guiding principle: a change includes its consequences","message":"## Proposal\n\nAdd a new guiding principle to `docs/PRINCIPLES.md`:\n\n\u003e **9. A change includes its consequences**\n\u003e\n\u003e Modifying code, configuration, or interfaces isn't done until tests, documentation,\n\u003e and dependent references reflect the change. Stale docs and broken tests fail quietly —\n\u003e treat them as part of the same work, not a follow-up task.\n\n## Rationale\n\nThis is distinct from Principle #3 (\"Capture decisions, not just implementations\"), which\nis specifically about recording *why* decisions were made so they don't get accidentally\nreverted. This new principle is about **completeness** — when something changes, everything\nthat describes, tests, or depends on it should be updated too.\n\nExamples of what \"consequences\" means across categories:\n\n| If you change... | Also update... |\n|------------------|----------------|\n| Code behavior | Tests that cover it |\n| Parameters/topics/services | Package docs, README, `.agents/README.md` |\n| API signatures | API docs, message/service definitions, callers |\n| User-facing behavior | User-facing docs |\n| Workspace rules | AGENTS.md, framework adapters, PR template |\n| Build structure | `package.xml`, `CMakeLists.txt`, `ARCHITECTURE.md` |\n| Scripts/Makefile | `make help` descriptions, script reference table |\n\n## Tiered enforcement\n\nThe principle should be exercised over time, not necessarily in a single PR. This is\nimportant for reducing friction with external contributors — accept the code contribution,\nfollow up on the polish.\n\n1. **At PR time (prompt, not gate)** — the PR template checklist prompts \"did you consider\n   what else needs updating?\" Best effort, not a blocking requirement.\n2. **At CI time (mechanical checks)** — obvious cases like source files changed but no\n   test files touched. See [Issue #265](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/265).\n3. **Periodically (review pass)** — scan recent merged PRs for gaps: code changed but\n   tests/docs didn't, new parameters without documentation, etc. Gaps become follow-up\n   issues, not reverts. This could eventually be automated (garbage collection agent\n   pattern from the #249 research, Appendix E).\n\n## Scope of work\n\n- Add principle #9 to `docs/PRINCIPLES.md`\n- Add a \"Documentation and test impact\" section to `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`\n  (non-blocking checklist)\n- Add corresponding guidance to AGENTS.md (Always section or Post-Task Verification)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}